                <li>
            <span class="who">
                <span class="">Henja Frydman</span>:
            </span>
            <span class="utterance" who="#frydmanH" start="6488.161" end="x">Always in a different manner. [Here we hear on the wire violent sneezing. If often happens that when an interviewee speaks of a certain condition that apparently evoked sneezing or coughing, he begins to sneeze or cough. We have that in the Frim spool, when the speaker begins to cough violently in the narrative about the disinfection of the clothes in the gas chamber.] Finished eating in a hurry, again back to work. In the afternoon it was arranged somewhat differently. They took us to the building, an abandoned structure, and we had to tear it up. They gave us a special too [she uses the French word for "crowbar"]--that is, a kind of thick stick.</span>
        </li>
                <li>
            <span class="who">
